cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CC 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category as it discusses a biologically plausible implementation of backprop in brains, which is a topic closely related to neural networks. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new framework for machine learning. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it discusses a learning rule for neural networks. The paper also touches on cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it discusses the propagation of perturbations backward in a network. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it discusses the computational requirements of the proposed framework.
